---
const credibility = [
  'founder, brokerloop (insurtech, melbourne au)',
  'production voice ai: outbound + inbound intake',
  'go backend systems · postgres · twilio · deepgram · pipecat',
  'consulting + commercial strategy background',
  'contract work by referral',
];
---
<section id="about" class="section reveal">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="prompt">&gt; ./about</div>
      <h2 class="h">About Jonathan</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="about">
        <p>I'm Jonathan. I'm the founder and senior engineer at Brokerloop, an Australian insurtech building automation infrastructure for insurance brokers — voice AI, long-form intake flows, and Go-based backend systems integrated with the platforms brokers actually use.</p>
        <p>I came up through full-stack engineering and consulting, which is a less common path into AI than the research route. It means I think about commercial constraints first — pricing, scope, what a system has to do when it breaks at 2am — and treat the model as one component of a working system rather than the point of it.</p>
        <p>Outside Brokerloop I take a small number of contracts each year, mostly in voice AI and backend AI infrastructure, for teams stuck in the gap between a working prototype and something that survives production.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pcard creds">
        <span class="corner tl"></span><span class="corner br"></span>
        <h4>// operator_log</h4>
        <ul>{credibility.map((c) => <li>{c}</li>)}</ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="ascii-div" aria-hidden="true">━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━</div>
  </div>
</section>
